main event: Unidentified flying objects (UFOs) were detected and analyzed on radar near Melville Air Station, Labrador on August 5, 1963.
interesting points: Two objects were observed approximately 2 miles apart and at altitudes fluctuating between 60,000 to 80,000 feet., Initial radar pickup was at a 1.12 degree azimuth with a range of 6 miles., The objects disappeared at a 166 degree azimuth at over 7 miles range., Two T-33 aircraft were scrambled but could not visually identify the objects., The phenomena were analyzed as possibly being high-speed aircraft or balloons under intelligent control.
witness description: Military personnel from the 61st AG Squadron and the Air Terper Squadron Command
